      "file_path": "utils-test/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/utils/io/Serializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "don't believe it's necessary, as ois.close() will invoke in.close().  In addition, it isn't necessary to invoke close on a ByteArrayInputStream.  Nevertheless, it's easy enough to include it in the try-with-resources.  Oddly, I expected jacoco to complain about not testing all of the exception paths when that was added, but it still seems happy with it for some reason.",
